<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>
        <%= examTitle %> | Instructions
    </title>
</head>
<style>
    /* Style the body */
    body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background-color: #f0f0f0;
    }

    /* Style the title heading */
    h1 {
        text-align: center;
        color: black;
        padding: 10px;
    }

    /* Style the container for instructions */
    .instruct {
        text-align: center;
        background-color: #fff;
        padding: 20px;
        margin: 20px;
        font-size: 16px;
        border-radius: 5px;
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
    }

    /* Style the paragraphs within the instructions */
    .instruct p {
        line-height: 1.6;
    }

    span {
        color: rgb(249, 187, 73);
    }

    button a{
        color: white;
        text-decoration: none;
    }

    /* Style the button */
    #btn {
        display: block;
        width: 150px;
        margin: 20px auto;
        background-color: rgb(249, 187, 73);
        color: #fff;
        border: none;
        font-size: 17px;
        padding: 10px;
        border-radius: 15px;
        cursor: pointer;
    }

    #btn:hover {
        background-color: rgb(248, 171, 29);
    }
</style>

<body>
    <h1> Instructions | <span>
            <%= examTitle %>
        </span>
    </h1>
    <div class="instruct">
        <pre>
            Before you begin your exam, it's essential to follow these instructions carefully to ensure a fair and
            smooth testing experience:

            1. **Arrival:** Arrive at the exam location well in advance. Ensure you have your student ID or any other
            required identification.

            2. **Materials:** Bring necessary materials only, such as pencils, pens, an eraser, and an approved
            calculator (if allowed).

            3. **Electronic Devices:** Power off and stow away all electronic devices, including phones, smartwatches,
            and tablets. These items should not be accessible during the exam.

            4. **Seating:** Sit at your assigned seat. Maintain a minimum distance from other students as instructed to
            prevent any possible cheating.

            5. **Exam Booklet:** Once seated, you'll receive your exam booklet and answer sheet. Check for any missing
            or misprinted pages.

            6. **Time Management:** Read the instructions and questions carefully. Note the total time for the exam and
            allocate your time wisely for each question.

            7. **Marking:** Use a pencil to mark your answers on the answer sheet clearly. Ensure that the question
            number and corresponding answer align correctly.

            Follow these instructions, and you'll be on your way to a successful MCQ exam. Good luck!
        </pre>
    </div>
    <button id="btn" type="submit"><a href="/startTest?examTitle=<%= examTitle %>">Start Test</a></button>
